Including Plots

You can also embed plots, for example:

Note that the echo = FALSE parameter was added to the code chunk to prevent printing of the R code that generated the plot.

set.seed(1) # it is often a good idea to set the random number seed so you can get
# the same simulated values on different sessions.
x<-arima.sim(n=1000,model=list(ar=c(0.7,0.2),ma=c(-0.3)))
# simulates from the ARIMA(2,0,1) model
ts.plot(x) # plot the time series

a1 <- acf(x,lag.max=30)$acf # plot the acf and

#store acf values for lags up to 30
a1 #print the values

ta1 <- ARMAacf(ar=c(0.7,0.2),ma=c(-0.3),lag.max=30)
# theoretical acf
plot(0:30,ta1,ylab="theoretical acf")

tp1 <- ARMAacf(ar=c(0.7,0.2),ma=c(-0.3),lag.max=30,pacf=TRUE)
# theoretical pacf
plot(1:30,tp1,ylab="theoretical pacf")

ta1 <- ARMAacf(ar=c(0.7,0.2),ma=c(-0.3),lag.max=30)
# theoretical acf
plot(0:30,ta1,ylab="theoretical acf")

tp1 <- ARMAacf(ar=c(0.7,0.2),ma=c(-0.3),lag.max=30,pacf=TRUE)
# theoretical pacf
plot(1:30,tp1,ylab="theoretical pacf")

acf(x,lag.max=30) #sample acf
lines(0:30, ta1, col=2) #overlay theoretical acf in red

pacf(x,lag.max=30) #sample pacf
lines(1:30, tp1, col=3) #overlay theoretical pacf in green
